subproject.description:
The project aim is to enhance the capacity of agricultural system in Ethiopia to adapt to climate change by developing and piloting a range of coping mechanisms for reducing the vulnerability of farmers and pastoralists. The project key results includes: Market oriented alternative livelihood strategies that enhance  resilience and income introduced and promoted  ; 
o	Production oriented sustainable land management/dry land farming  practices introduced and promoted ;
o	Integrated drought information communication system established;
o	Capacity of community level institutions for climate information and risk management  enhanced;
o	Capacity of local meteorological institutions developed;
o	Farmers/agro-pastoralist outside the pilot kebeles are exposed to successful approaches and practices of the pilot kebeles.

